    "text": "The online hidden-target learning algorithm used for inventory optimization can be adapted to model the temporal evolution of the planetesimal formation threshold in a dissipating gas disk, predicting that the Kuiper cliff arises from an exponentially drifting density boundary, falsified if the predicted edge profile does not match observed CCKBO distributions.",
    "topic": "online optimization of disk dissipation"
  },
  {
    "text": "The controlled composition scaffold from AgentSpec, which preserves core behaviors under perturbation, can be applied to maintain long-term memory stability in continual learning systems by isolating and freezing certain parameter subspaces (analogous to CCKBOs), and it will reduce catastrophic drift; this is falsified if isolating random subspaces works equally well.",
    "topic": "scaffolded memory against drift"
  }
